Citation.sTitle: Volumetric and Viscometric Studies of Antidepressant Drugs in Aqueous Medium at Different Temperatures
Citation.sAbstract: Notriptyline hydrochloride and trimipramine maleate are used as antidepressants and analgesics. The density and viscosity of the aqueous solutions of these compounds are measured in a range of molality, m ) (9.7 E 10-6 to 32.5 E 10-6) mol E g-1, at T ) (293.15 to 313.15) K using a commercial densimeter and viscometer. The apparent molar volume (V O), partial molar volume (Vm 0 ), partial molar expansivity (E2 0 ), thermal expansion coefficient (R2), and Hepler fs constant ( Y2Vm 0 / YT2) are calculated from the density data. The values of the B-coefficient and hydration number (Hn) are computed from the viscosity data.
